---
import Base from "../../../layouts/Base.astro";
import CTASection from "../../../components/CTASection.astro";
import FosterModal from "../../../components/FosterModal.astro";
---

<Base title="Foster Care | Homeless Hounds Animal Rescue">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="relative isolate overflow-hidden bg-white min-h-[50vh] flex items-center">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-500 to-teal-700"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-pattern-dots opacity-10"></div>

      <div class="container-custom py-20 md:py-24 relative z-10">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
          <p class="text-white/80 text-sm uppercase tracking-widest font-semibold mb-4">Open your heart and home</p>
          <h1 class="text-white mb-6 text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold">
            Foster <span class="text-orange-400">Care</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-white/90 mb-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            Foster care saves lives. By opening your home temporarily, you help animals recover, heal and prepare for their forever homes.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
            <a href="#application" class="btn btn-white">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                <path d="M10.707 2.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 0l-7 7a1 1 0 001.414 1.414L4 10.414V17a1 1 0 001 1h2a1 1 0 001-1v-2a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v2a1 1 0 001 1h2a1 1 0 001-1v-6.586l.293.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414l-7-7z" />
              </svg>
              Apply to Foster
            </a>
            <a href="/contact-us" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border-2 border-white text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-teal-600 transition-all duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-white focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-offset-teal-600">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
              Learn More
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

      <!-- Why Foster Section -->
      <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Why should I become a foster carer?</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700">
          <p class="mb-6">
            Foster carers are the backbone of our rescue operations. Without foster homes, we simply cannot save as many animals.
            By fostering, you're providing a safe, loving environment where animals can recover from trauma, illness, or surgery,
            and learn to trust humans again.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-6">
            Many of the animals that come into our care need time to decompress and heal – something that's difficult to achieve
            in a shelter environment. Foster homes provide the peace, quiet, and individual attention these animals need to flourish.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-6">
            Foster care is also incredibly rewarding. You get to witness an animal's transformation from scared and uncertain
            to confident and ready for adoption. You're literally saving lives and giving animals a second chance at happiness.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Animals Needing Help -->
      <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Animals That Need Foster Care</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

          <div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-700 pl-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Pregnant Animals</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              Expecting mothers need a quiet, stress-free environment to give birth and raise their babies safely.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-700 pl-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Mothers with Babies</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              New mothers and their offspring need a calm environment during those crucial first weeks of life.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-700 pl-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Medical Recovery</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              Animals recovering from surgery or illness need a quiet place to heal with monitoring and care.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-700 pl-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Behavioural Rehabilitation</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              Some animals need help learning to trust humans again or basic house training and socialisation.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-700 pl-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Emergency Care</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              When shelters are full or animals need immediate help, foster homes provide life-saving temporary accommodation.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-700 pl-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Senior Animals</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              Older animals often struggle in shelter environments and thrive in the comfort of a loving foster home.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Foster Care FAQ -->
      <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">

          <!-- FAQ 1 -->
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
            <button
              onclick="toggleAccordion('faq-1')"
              class="w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors group"
            >
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 group-hover:text-teal-700">
                How long do animals stay in foster care?
              </h4>
              <svg id="faq-1-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7 7"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>
            <div id="faq-1-content" class="hidden">
              <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white">
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  Foster periods vary depending on the animal's needs. It could be a few weeks for a healthy animal
                  waiting for adoption, several months for a mother with babies, or longer for animals requiring
                  medical treatment or behavioural rehabilitation. We'll always discuss the expected timeframe with you beforehand.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ 2 -->
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
            <button
              onclick="toggleAccordion('faq-2')"
              class="w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors group"
            >
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 group-hover:text-teal-700">
                What support do foster carers receive?
              </h4>
              <svg id="faq-2-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7 7"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>
            <div id="faq-2-content" class="hidden">
              <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white">
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  Homeless Hounds covers all veterinary expenses and provides food, bedding, toys, and any other
                  supplies needed. You'll have 24/7 access to our support team and experienced volunteers for advice
                  and assistance. We also provide training and resources to help you succeed as a foster carer.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ 3 -->
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
            <button
              onclick="toggleAccordion('faq-3')"
              class="w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors group"
            >
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 group-hover:text-teal-700">
                What if I fall in love with my foster animal?
              </h4>
              <svg id="faq-3-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7 7"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>
            <div id="faq-3-content" class="hidden">
              <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white">
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  Foster carers have first option to adopt their foster animals! Many of our volunteers have become
                  "foster failures" – and we couldn't be happier. If you decide to adopt, you'll go through the same
                  adoption process as any other applicant to ensure it's the right match.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQ 4 -->
          <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
            <button
              onclick="toggleAccordion('faq-4')"
              class="w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors group"
            >
              <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 group-hover:text-teal-700">
                Do I need experience with animals to foster?
              </h4>
              <svg id="faq-4-icon" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 transform transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7 7"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>
            <div id="faq-4-content" class="hidden">
              <div class="px-6 py-4 bg-white">
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  While experience is helpful, it's not essential. What matters most is your commitment, patience, and
                  willingness to learn. We provide comprehensive support and training to all our foster carers, regardless
                  of their experience level. We'll match you with animals that suit your comfort level and experience.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Application Information -->
      <section id="application" class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Ready to Start Fostering?</h3>
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 mb-8">
          <p class="mb-4">
            If you're ready to make a difference in an animal's life, we'd love to hear from you.
            The application process helps us understand your living situation, experience, and preferences
            so we can match you with the right animals.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-6">
            We have separate application processes for dog and cat foster carers, as the requirements
            and considerations can be different for each type of animal. Choose the application that best
            suits your interests below.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Foster Application Options -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <!-- Dog Foster Application -->
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-white border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-4 shadow-lg">
                <span class="text-2xl">🐕</span>
              </div>
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Dog Foster Care</h4>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              Foster dogs of all ages, from puppies to seniors. Perfect for those who enjoy active companionship and daily walks.
            </p>
            <button
              onclick="openDogFosterModal()"
              class="w-full bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-blue-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg hover:from-blue-700 hover:to-blue-800 transition-colors flex items-center justify-center"
            >
